## Objective
To understand NumPy fundamentals required for machine learning and data preprocessing.

## Topics Covered
- Introduction to NumPy
- Creating NumPy arrays (1D & 2D)
- Array properties (shape, size, dtype)
- Mathematical operations (mean, max, min, std)
- Vectorized operations
- Boolean masking and filtering
- Indexing and slicing
- Reshaping arrays for ML models

## Practice Tasks
- Age and salary dataset creation
- Feature extraction using NumPy slicing
- Data filtering using boolean conditions
- Marks classification task

## ML Connection
NumPy is the backbone of:
- Data preprocessing
- Feature scaling
- Mathematical computations
- Model input preparation

